raw_data.description: We're a specialty coffee shop, our primary emphasis lies in delivering exceptional, top-tier coffee of the highest quality.

reviews_data.review_text: A lot of traffic but if you don’t mind it it’s fine.
We love WaterBean it’s our go to every Friday morning! We get bacon, egg, and provolone cheese sandwiches on a croissant with their special sauce. So delicious. And the matcha ain’t bad, either!
I arrived early for a doctor's appointment and enjoyed an amazing cup of coffee this morning.  The service was awesome and I loved the atmosphere.

I ordered a drink that is similar to what I get from Starbucks. I don’t like all the extras. Just some espresso, almond milk and a little flavor. My main intent is to get that pick me up & to not spend too much.

She insisted on making two drink options that costed at least $5 more than what I got, not including the price of two more espresso shots. I’m glad I asked the price before agreeing! Once I shot that down I still thanked her with a smile but you could immediately tell she still got offended. I tipped her still. I said thank you twice. Nothing. Grabbed my drink, have a good day. Nothing. Why do customer service to begin with. I would happily take my money back if I could & am glad I didn’t tip more because it’s the privilege for me. It was my first time here so that also adds to it.

One star service but two stars for the tasty Rice Krispie treat, the cookies n cream macaroon, & the great & fresh taste of the espresso. Nice sized cafe inside with plenty of seating. Will go back but to a different location

This place never seems to show up when searching "coffee" on Google Maps but it's a great option.  The coffee is well-made, they have an app in which you can order ahead and earn points (but doesn't allow you to pay with Google Pay).  They have some really amazing custom drinks.  Breakfast sandwiches are good and reasonably priced for the area.  It's an office and apartment location so you see a mix from joggers to well-dressed consultants.
Amazing coffee with lots of choices. Salmon bagel was incredible and atmosphere was good!

Do not get an espresso here. Made a terrible mistake when I didn’t have time to make one at home. They don’t have a real espresso machine here just “we tell the machine what to do and it makes it” I should’ve walked out when the cashier seemed surprised by my order.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Pat,

Thank you for your feedback. We'd like to clarify a few points about our espresso machine and processes. We use the Epic Espresso Machine from Unic, a top-of-the-line model made in France. This machine allows us to precisely control temperature, water volume, and pressure, and it features ThermalLink technology and independent boiler variation. It's far from a simple push-button operation.

Our grinders are five E65s from Mahlkönig, which are highly regarded in the coffee industry. Additionally, we roast all of our coffee in-house at our certified USDA organic facility. We manually tamp and weigh everything by scale to ensure quality.

Our espresso is crafted with care and precision, and we also use a reverse osmosis water filtration system, which many establishments avoid due to its cost.

Please consider these details when providing feedback. We value respectful and unbiased reviews.

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was very good. Make your own hot sandwich was fantastic and a good price.  Service was friendly and excellent.  I would highly recommend.
Chill coffee spot with delicious breakfast sandwiches. Online ordering is very convenient.
I come here just about every day. Friendly staff and great coffee!
Nice

A little bit difficult to find on your first time, but otherwise great. The inside is very nice, very modern but cozy. The staff is great. They have multiple beans and roasts to choose from and they let you decide which one you want. First time I’ve been to a coffee shop here in Charlotte that would let you choose between 5 different bean options.
This place is perfect
Loved the decor and my latte was great. Barista was so friendly as well.
Very great peach refresher and the barista was nice and had a great playlist.
I am so glad this one has opened up, it is our favorite place to go for coffee!

Their coffee is absolutely incredible. Breakfast sandwiches are just as good. 10/10, maybe an 11/10. Staff is so helpful and nice. Their specialty drinks are some of the best coffee drinks I have had. Worth the extra $1 or $2.
